    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. but what about when those mandates actually cause real harm to people's core identities or lives? if the state forces a group to act against their deepest convictions, isn't that just a form of state-sponsored oppression? how do you weigh that against the \"impartial rule of law\"?",
